Not really, effectively all liquid fossil fuels is composed of plant or aquatic animal material that formed 300-400 million years ago or earlier about 100-200 million years before the early Triassic when the first (proto-)dinosaurs started to show up so the gas you put in your car'd be more likely to be possessed by a trilobite than a dinosaur.

And there's the fact dinosaurs have more in common with birds than reptiles (birds being the descendants of a branch of the dinosaur phylum(Class? Or is it Order? Highschool Bio was a long time ago might be a bit iffy since their reptillianity is quite arguable.

Long story short the science is pretty stacked against this skip in my opinion, poor little thing that it is.







